{{Infobox language |name=Iznasen |altname=Eastern Riffian |nativename=''Beni Iznasen'' |states=[[Morocco]] |region=extreme northeast |speakers=100,000 |date=2013 |ref=<ref name=Kossmann>Maarten Kossmann (2013) [https://books.google.fr/books?id=Se-BAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA23#v=snippet&q=%22eastern%20Riffian%22&f=false The Arabic Influence on Northern Berber]</ref> |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Berber languages|Berber]] |fam3=[[Northern Berber languages|Northern Berber]] |fam4=[[Zenati languages|Zenati]] |iso3=none |glotto=beni1249 |glottorefname=Beni Iznassen }}
'''Iznasen''' ('''Iznassen''', '''Iznacen''') is a [[Berber languages|Berber]] language, one of the [[Zenati languages]]. It is spoken in the extreme northeast of [[Morocco]], in a speech area near that of [[Riffian language|Riffian]] and the Berber languages of western [[Algeria]].
