{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
The '''live crown''' is the top part of a [[tree]], the part that has green [[leaves]] (as opposed to the bare [[trunk (botany)|trunk]], bare [[branches]], and dead leaves).  The ratio of the size of a tree's live crown to its total height is used in estimating its health and its level of competition with neighboring trees.

