{{Infobox language |name=Mpi |nativename=Kaw |states=[[Thailand]], perhaps [[China]] |region= |ethnicity=1,500 (2007)<ref name=e18/> |speakers=900 |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern Loloish]] |fam6= |iso3=mpz |glotto=mpii1239 |glottorefname=Mpi }}
'''Mpi''' is a [[Loloish language]] of [[Thailand]]. The number of speakers is in decline. It is spoken in the following two villages in northern [[Thailand]].
*Ban Dong, Tambon Suan Khuean สวนเขื่อน, [[Mueang Phrae District]], [[Phrae Province]] (autonym: ''m̩33 pi53'' in Ban Dong) *Ban Sakoeng, Tambon Yot ยอด, [[Song Khwae District]], [[Nan Province]] (autonym: ''kɔ53'' Ban Sakoeng)
Since the [[Mpi people|Mpi]] of Thailand migrated from [[Mengla]], [[Xishuangbanna]], Yunnan, China over 300 years ago, there could also possibly be Mpi speakers in China (Nahhas 2007).
==Phonology== Mpi has six [[tone (linguistics)|tones]] and two [[phonation]]s in its [[vowel]]s, [[modal voice]] and [[stiff voice]]:
{|class="wikitable IPA" !Tone!!Modal voice!!Stiff voice |- !Low | sì 'blood' || sì̬ 'seven' |- !Low rising | si᷅ 'putrid' || si̬᷅ 'dried up' |- !Mid | sī (a color)|| sī̬ (a [[noun classifier|classifier]]) |- !Mid rising | sǐ 'to roll' || sǐ̬ 'to smoke' |- !High | sí 'four' || sí̬ (a name) |- !High rising | si᷄ 'to die' || si̬᷄ (a name) |}
