{{Infobox language |name=Rendille |states=[[Kenya]] |region=[[Eastern Province (Kenya)|Eastern Province]] |speakers=60,000 |date=2009 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Cushitic languages|Cushitic]] |fam3=[[Lowland East Cushitic languages|Lowland East]] |fam4=[[Rendille–Boni languages|Rendille–Boni]] |iso3=rel |glotto=rend1243 |glottorefname=Rendille }} '''Rendille''' (also known as '''Rendile''', '''Randile''') is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken by the [[Rendille people]] inhabiting northern [[Kenya]]. It is part of the family's [[Cushitic languages|Cushitic]] branch.<ref name="Ethnren">[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=rel Ethnologue - Rendille]</ref>
The [[Ariaal people|Ariaal]] sub-group of the Rendille, who are of mixed [[Nilotic peoples|Nilotic]] and Cushitic descent, speak the [[Nilo-Saharan languages|Nilo-Saharan]] [[Samburu language]] of the [[Samburu people|Samburu]] Nilotes near whom they live.<ref name="Ethnren"/><ref name="Parris">{{cite book|last=Parris|first=Ronald G.|title=Rendille|year=1994|publisher=Rosen Publishing Group|isbn=0823917630|pages=13}}</ref>
